### Enhancements

* `conda init xonsh` on Windows: replace the `if !(test -f "...")` guard
  (which silently no-ops because `test` is not on bare Windows) with a
  pythonic `pathlib.Path("...").is_file()` check, and use
  `backslash_to_forwardslash` instead of `win_path_to_unix` so the rendered
  path stays Windows-native (`C:/...`) instead of MSYS-style (`/c/...`)
  that needs cygpath. (xonsh/xonsh#3676)

### Bug fixes

* `XonshActivator`: route `template_export_var` and `template_set_var`
  through `path_conversion` so `CONDA_PREFIX`, `CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV` and
  `CONDA_PROMPT_MODIFIER` no longer emit raw Windows paths inside Python
  single-quoted literals. The xonsh output is exec'd as Python, so a
  backslash like `\U` (in `C:\Users\…`) or `\n` / `\t` would otherwise
  trigger a `SyntaxError` on the very first `conda activate <env>`.
  (xonsh/xonsh#3676)

